{"id": 6381, "title": "Ticket #6381: getConsoleWindowSize() checks input rather than output", "description": "<blockquote>\ncondor_status calls getConsoleWindowSize() to determine both width and if its output is printed to a pipe but its ioctl() is run against stdin.  This causes condor_status to misformat its output if it's piped into, rather than out of.\n\n<p>This code is duplicated in three other tools (_who, _q, and _history), who exclusively (erroneously?) care about width.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2017-Aug-23 14:07:42 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\nIt looks like the callers in all but one place were already coded to allow for a negative return size.  For that one place, I replaced the direct call at queue.cpp line 5489 to getConsoleWindowSize() with a call to an existing wrapper function that would return a default size if the width was actually negative.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Sep-12 09:38:51 by johnkn:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE_REVIEW</strong> : changes look good to me.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Oct-06 01:46:31 by tannenba:</em> <br/>\n\nWhy patch v8.7 instead of v8.6? Also please (always) fill in the broken version field on defect tickets.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Oct-06 11:28:33 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\nLet's cherry-pick this back to 8.6\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Oct-09 17:07:15 by tlmiller:</em> <br/>\n\nMoved release note from 8.7 to 8.6.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Oct-20 17:07:15 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>CODE REVIEW</strong>: Looks good.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2017-Oct-25 10:23:31 by tim:</em> <br/>\n\n<strong>DOC Review:</strong> OK</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2017-Oct-10 11:53</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span cl